  "title": "Business Development Manager (Lighting)",
  "description": "<p><strong>i) Sales and Marketing of the Company’s Products and Services:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Drive business development by acquiring new customers and initiating new projects.</li>\n  <li>Maintain and strengthen relationships with existing clients.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with Lighting Consultants, Architects, Interior Designers, and other stakeholders on lighting specifications.</li>\n  <li>Promote the Koizumi brand and enhance product awareness in the market.</li>\n  <li>Prepare marketing materials and presentations.</li>\n  <li>Conduct live demonstrations and presentations, highlighting key product features.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>ii) Handling Company-Generated Sales Enquiries:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Participate in site visits, walk-throughs, and surveys.</li>\n  <li>Prepare sales quotations and tender submissions.</li>\n  <li>Follow up on enquiries through calls and email correspondence.</li>\n  <li>Assist clients in resolving issues related to product usage.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>iii) After-Sales Service:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversee project execution, monitor progress, and ensure successful and timely completion.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate effectively with a multidisciplinary team, including consultants and external subcontractors.</li>\n  <li>Provide accurate and timely project updates to the management team.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma holder in Electrical / Electronic Engineering or Marketing.</li>\n  <li>Preferable 3 years’ experience as a Sales in construction material industry</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110981</p>\n<p>EA Personnel Name: Law Mei Fong</p>",
